cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SD 

The paper discusses the design principles of boolean logic gates in unconventional computers, specifically using NMR-based case study. This falls under the category of Emerging Technologies (cs.ET) as unconventional computers are still in the early stages of development. Additionally, the paper involves the use of algorithms and computational complexity theory, which falls under the category of Architecture (cs.AR) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses programming languages and compilers, which falls under the category of Programming Languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper involves the use of simulation and modeling, which falls under the category of Software Engineering (cs.SD).
